rComments: The class is tough, but the curve is very much in your favor. Everyone did poorly on one exam, so he let the final replace the midterm.

As stated earlier for the 2nd exam he handed out practice problem but did not post solutions. Not a huge deal... This class was intense. We quickly out paced similar classes and covered more material. On his "off" days he can be quite curt with classes, otherwise class experience is great, if a little rushed. Participate in class and you'll do fine

Get ready to work your butt off. This guy will release practice exams and not give you solutions. Prepare for unforgivable grading techniques and difficult exams. No curves, no extra credit, however the grading scale is altered to the students favor (i.e. >80 A ...>70 B) .
